fields.title: KEDARNATH
fields.address: DISTRICT OF UTTARAKHAND 86 KM OF RUDHRAPRAYAG
fields.desc:
Arrive in Rishikesh and check into your hotel.
Spend the afternoon exploring Rishikesh, a spiritual city known for its yoga and meditation centers.
In the evening, take a boat ride on the Ganges River.

Drive to Sonprayag, the starting point for the trek to Kedarnath.
Take a jeep or taxi to Gaurikund, the last motorable road to Kedarnath.
Start the trek to Kedarnath (16 kilometers, 5-6 hours).
Arrive in Kedarnath and visit the Kedarnath Temple, a 12th-century Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva.

Spend the morning in Kedarnath.
Trek back to Gaurikund (16 kilometers, 5-6 hours).
Drive back to Rishikesh.

fields.title: TAJ-MAHAL
fields.address: 230 KM SOUTH EAST OF THE NATIONAL CAPITAL DELHI
fields.desc:
Arrive in Agra and check into your hotel.
Visit the Taj Mahal in the afternoon. The best time to visit is early in the morning or late in the evening, when the crowds are smaller.
Take a guided tour of the Taj Mahal to learn about its history and architecture.
Visit the Mehtab Bagh, a garden located across the river from the Taj Mahal. It is a popular spot for viewing the Taj Mahal at sunset.

fields.title: JAISALMER
fields.desc:
Arrive in Jaisalmer and check into your hotel.
Visit the Jaisalmer Fort, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. It is a massive fort made of yellow sandstone.
Take a stroll through the old city, a maze of narrow streets and alleyways.
Visit the Patwon Ki Haveli, a beautifully decorated haveli (mansion).
Go on a camel safari in the Thar Desert.
Visit the Sam Sand Dunes, the tallest dunes in the Thar Desert.
Enjoy a sunset camel ride and sand dune bashing.

fields.title: Kerala
fields.desc:
Arrive in Kochi and check into your hotel.Munnar: This is a hill station known for its lush tea plantations and stunning mountain views. You can go for a hike or visit the Eravikulam National Park.
Kovalam: This is a beach resort town known for its beautiful beaches and laid-back atmosphere. You can go for a swim in the Arabian Sea or relax on the beach.
Kochi: This is a historic city known for its Fort Kochi and Chinese fishing nets. You can take a walk around the city or visit the Mattancherry Palace.

fields.title: KULLU-MANALI
fields.address: IN THE STATE OF HIMACHAL PRADESH
fields.desc:
Arrive in Manali and check into your hotel.
Visit the Hadimba Devi Temple, a 16th-century temple dedicated to the goddess Hadimba.
Take a walk around the Mall Road, a popular shopping and dining area.
Enjoy the views of the surrounding mountains.
Go for a hike to Solang Valley, a beautiful valley with snow-capped mountains.
Try out some adventure activities, such as paragliding or rafting.
Visit the Manu Temple, a 10th-century temple dedicated to the sage Manu.

fields.title: GOA
fields.address: Goa is a state in western india capital is PANAJI
fields.desc:
Arrive in Goa and check into your hotel in Panaji, the capital of Goa.
Visit the Basilica of Bom Jesus, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.
Take a walk around the Fontainhas area, a charming Portuguese-style neighborhood.
Go for a beach picnic at Anjuna Beach, one of the most popular beaches in Goa.
Try out some water sports, such as parasailing or jet skiing.
Visit the flea market in Anjuna, a great place to buy souvenirs and local handicrafts.
Take a day trip to Old Goa, a former Portuguese colony.
Visit the Se Cathedral, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.

fields.title: NAINITAL
fields.desc:
Arrive in Nainital and check into your hotel.
Visit the Nainital Lake, a beautiful lake surrounded by snow-capped mountains.
Take a boat ride on the lake or go for a swim.
Visit the Naina Devi Temple, a Hindu temple dedicated to the goddess Naina Devi.
Go for a hike to Snow View, a viewpoint located at the top of Naina Devi Hill.
Enjoy the stunning views of the surrounding mountains.
Visit the Jim Corbett National Park, a national park located about 70 kilometers from Nainital.

fields.title: Sikkim
fields.address: SIKKIM IS A STATE IN NORTHEST INDIA ,BORDERED BY BHUTAN,TIBET,AND NEPAL
fields.desc:
Arrive in Gangtok, the capital of Sikkim. Check into your hotel and relax for a while.
Visit the Hanuman Tok, a viewpoint that offers stunning views of the city. Visit the Enchey Monastery, a Buddhist monastery located in Gangtok. Go for a hike to the Tashi Viewpoint, which offers panoramic views of the city and the surrounding mountains. Visit the Namgyal Institute of Tibetology, a research institute dedicated to the study of Tibetan Buddhism. Take a day trip to Nathula Pass, a high-altitude pass located on the border between India and China.

fields.title: Mahakal
fields.address: Ujjain is city in ujjain district of the indian state of madhyapradesh
fields.desc:
Arrive in Ujjain and check into your hotel. Visit the Mahakaleshwar Temple, a 10th-century temple dedicated to Lord Shiva. Take a walk around the old city and explore the temples and bazaars. Visit the Omkareshwar Temple, a 12th-century temple located on an island in the Narmada River.Take a boat ride on the Narmada River and enjoy the beautiful scenery.
Visit the Kal Bhairav Temple, a temple dedicated to the fearsome form of Lord Shiva.

fields.title: Golden Temple
fields.address: Amritsar is a city of Punjab
fields.desc:
Arrive in Amritsar and check into your hotel.
Visit the Golden Temple, a Sikh Gurdwara (temple) that is considered to be the holiest place in Sikhism.Take a walk around the temple complex and admire the beautiful architecture.
Enjoy a free meal (langar) at the temple. Visit the Jallianwala Bagh, a historical site where hundreds of unarmed civilians were killed by British troops in 1919. Take a walk around the park and pay your respects to the victims.
Visit the Wagah Border, a border crossing between India and Pakistan.
